Norwegian oil group Statoil said on Monday that it was trying to seal off a gas leak on a platform in the North Sea where production had been suspended and most employees evacuated owing to the risk of an explosion.
At the moment it is unclear when production from Snorre A and Vigdis will resume, Statoil said in a statement.
On November 28, the company shut down Snorre A after a gas leak was detected.
Norway's oil production has been reduced by some 205,000 barrels per day.
